        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 6:23AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Visibility in the valleys of Southwestern Montana south of I-90
is reduced due to rain and/or fog. Visibility is as low as 3
miles or less. Visibility will gradually improved over the next
few hours.

If traveling in Southwestern Montana this morning use caution,
slow down, be prepared for changing visibility, and make sure
your headlights are on.
</description>
